# Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge

We as contributors and maintainers pledge to make participation in this project a respectful, welcoming, and harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of background, location, or experience level.

## Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment include:

- Using welcoming and inclusive language  
- Respecting different viewpoints and experiences  
- Offering and accepting constructive feedback graciously  
- Focusing on the value of shared knowledge and collaboration  

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

- Harassment, discrimination, or insulting remarks  
- Personal or political attacks  
- Publishing private or sensitive information without consent  
- Any conduct that disrupts the community or makes others feel unsafe  

## Our Responsibilities

Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying and enforcing this Code of Conduct and may take appropriate and fair corrective action in response to any behavior that violates it.

## Scope

This Code of Conduct applies in all project spaces, including issues, pull requests, discussions, and any other form of communication related to the project.

## Enforcement

Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported by contacting the maintainers at [digitalpr@stirupopportunity.com]. All reports will be handled confidentially and reviewed promptly.

## Attribution

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.1, available at [https://www.contributor-covenant.org](https://www.contributor-covenant.org).
